chunks.html_content: You must tell DVLA if you have an eating disorder (for example anorexia nervosa) and it affects your ability to drive safely.
chunks.plain_content:
Eating disorders and driving
You must tell DVLA if you have an eating disorder (for example anorexia nervosa) and it affects your ability to drive safely.

chunks.html_content: You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.
chunks.plain_content:
Eating disorders and driving
You can be fined up to £1,000 if you don’t tell DVLA about a medical condition that affects your driving. You may be prosecuted if you’re involved in an accident as a result.

chunks.html_content:
Ask your doctor if you’re not sure if your eating disorder will affect your driving.

You must tell DVLA if your condition will affect your driving. Fill in form M1 and send it to DVLA. The address is on the form.
